<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EEC) No 2903/79 of 20 December 1979 on the downgrading of quality wines produced in specified regions </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 2903/79 m&auml;&auml;ratletud piirkonnas valmistatud kvaliteetveini klassi alandamise kohta 20. detsember 1979 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 337/79 of 5 February 1979 on the common organization of the market in wine (1), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 2594/79 (2), and in particular Articles 53 (3) and 65 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 5. veebruari 1979. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 337/79 veinituru &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 2594/79, eriti selle artikli 53 l&otilde;iget 3 ja artiklit 65, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 338/79 of 5 February 1979 laying down special provisions relating to quality wines produced in specified regions (3), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 2594/79, and in particular Article 16 (7) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 5. veebruari 1979. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 338/79, millega n&auml;hakse ette eris&auml;tted m&auml;&auml;ratletud piirkonnas valmistatud kvaliteetveinide kohta, viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 2594/79, eriti selle artikli 16 l&otilde;iget 7, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, pursuant to Article 16 (6) of Regulation (EEC) No 338/79, a quality wine psr may be downgraded at the marketing stage in certain circumstances only; whereas these circumstances should be specified and the use to which quality wines psr so downgraded may be put should be stated and limited; whereas the competent authorities having the right to downgrade pursuant to Article 2 (1) or, as appropriate, Article 2 (3) of Regulation (EEC) No 460/79 (4) should also be indicated; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 338/79 artikli 16 l&otilde;ikele 6 v&otilde;ib mpv-kvaliteetveini klassi alandada turustusetapil &uuml;ksnes teatavatel asjaoludel; need asjaolud tuleks kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata ning sel viisil alandatud klassiga mpv-kvaliteetveinide kasutamine tuleks s&auml;testada ja piiritleda; tuleks m&auml;&auml;rata ka p&auml;devad asutused, kellel on vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 460/79 artikli 2 l&otilde;ikele 1 v&otilde;i vajaduse korral artikli 2 l&otilde;ikele 3 &otilde;igus klassi alandada; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in order to ensure that consumers are not misled, a downgraded quality wine psr should not be marketed under a designation which suggests the designation to which it no longer is entitled; whereas, so that proper control may be carried out, entries should be made in movement registers to show that downgrading has taken place; </inglise>
<eesti> tagamaks, et tarbijaid ei eksitata, ei tohiks alandatud klassiga mpv-kvaliteetveini enam turustada nimetuse all, mis viitab nimetusele, millele sellel veinil ei ole enam &otilde;igust; n&otilde;uetekohase kontrolli v&otilde;imaldamiseks tuleb kaupade liikumise registrisse teha kanded, mis n&auml;itaksid, et on toimunud klassi alandamine; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in order that the Commission may be kept aware of the way in which the competent authorities of the Member States apply the provisions on the downgrading of quality wines psr, the Member States should communicate to the Commission each year the quantities of quality wines psr which were downgraded on their geographical territory; </inglise>
<eesti> teavitamaks komisjoni sellest, kuidas liikmesriikide p&auml;devad asutused kohaldavad mpv-kvaliteetveinide klassi alandamise s&auml;tteid, peaksid liikmesriigid teatama komisjonile igal aastal mpv-kvaliteetveinide kogused, mille klassi alandati nende geograafilisel territooriumil; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the rules provided for in this Regulation incorporate and supplement those of Regulation (EEC) No 1697/70 (5); whereas that Regulation should therefore be repealed; </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud eeskirjad kattuvad m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 1697/70 s&auml;testatud eeskirjadega ja t&auml;iendavad neid; sellep&auml;rast tuleks see m&auml;&auml;rus kehtetuks tunnistada; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Wine, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las veinituru korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The downgrading of a quality wine psr within the meaning of this Regulation shall consist in withdrawing from the wine concerned entitlement to any of the terms designating it a quality wine psr. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses t&auml;hendab mpv-kvaliteetveini klassi alandamine asjaomase veini puhul, et on &auml;ra v&otilde;etud &otilde;igus kasutada m&auml;rkeid, mis n&auml;itaksid, et tegemist on mpv-kvaliteetveiniga. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> A quality wine psr may be downgraded at the marketing stage only by the bodies designated for this purpose by the Member States: - to a table wine, </inglise>
<eesti> Vaid liikmesriikide poolt sellel eesm&auml;rgil m&auml;&auml;ratud asutused v&otilde;ivad turustusetapil alandada mpv-kvaliteetveini klassi: - lauaveiniks, </eesti>
<inglise> - to a wine suitable for yielding table wine, or </inglise>
<eesti> - lauaveini valmistamiseks sobivaks veiniks, </eesti>
<inglise> - to a wine not covered by the above indents. </inglise>
<eesti> - eelmistes alapunktides nimetamata veiniks. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> At the marketing stage a quality wine psr may be downgraded where an official analytical or organoleptic examination reveals that a deterioration found in the course of ageing, storage or transport has weakened or altered the characteristics of that wine in such a way that it no longer possesses the characteristics typical of the quality wine psr in question. </inglise>
<eesti> Turustusetapil v&otilde;ib mpv-kvaliteetveini klassi alandada, kui ametlik anal&uuml;&uuml;s v&otilde;i organoleptiline hindamine n&auml;itab, et laagerdumise, ladustamise v&otilde;i transpordi ajal toimunud kvaliteedi halvenemine on n&otilde;rgendanud v&otilde;i muutnud selle veini omadusi nii, et sellel veinil ei ole enam k&otilde;nealuse mpv-kvaliteetveini t&uuml;&uuml;pilisi omadusi. </eesti>
<inglise> A quality wine psr shall in particular be considered as having undergone deterioration justifying its downgrading whether it has been found: (a) that it no longer meets the requirements relating to at least one of the characteristic features referred to in Article 14 of Regulation (EEC) No 338/79; or </inglise>
<eesti> Mpv-kvaliteetveini k&auml;sitletakse halvenenuna, nii et see &otilde;igustaks selle &uuml;mberhindamist, kui leitakse, et: a) vein ei vasta enam v&auml;hemalt &uuml;hele m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 338/79 artiklis 14 osutatud omadusele v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> (b) that it no longer possesses the colour, clarity, smell or taste which normally distinguish a quality wine psr originating from the region whose name it bears. </inglise>
<eesti> b) veinil ei ole enam v&auml;rvust, selgust, l&otilde;hna v&otilde;i maitset, mis on tavaliselt omased mpv-kvaliteetveinile, mis p&auml;rineb piirkonnast, mille nime ta kannab. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The downgrading of a quality wine psr at the marketing stage shall be pronouced by the competent body referred to, as the case may be, in Article 2 (1) or (3) of Regulation (EEC) No 460/79. </inglise>
<eesti> Mpv-kvaliteetveini klassi alandamise otsustab turustusetapil p&auml;dev asutus, millele on osutatud vastavalt vajadusele m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 460/79 artikli 2 l&otilde;ikes 1 v&otilde;i 3. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The procedure for downgrading a quality wine psr shall be opened on the initiative: (a) of the competent body, at the time of any appropriate check; or </inglise>
<eesti> Mpv-kvaliteetveini klassi alandamise algatab: a) p&auml;dev asutus mis tahes asjakohase kontrolli ajal v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> (b) of the trader in possession of the wine if he finds that the case set out in Article 2 (2) has arisen. </inglise>
<eesti> b) kaupleja, kelle valduses see vein on, kui ta leiab, et on tekkinud artikli 2 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud olukord. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The names and addresses of the competent bodies authorized by the Member States to carry out the downgrading of a quality wine psr are set out in the Annex. </inglise>
<eesti> Nende p&auml;devate asutuste nimed ja aadressid, keda liikmesriigid on volitanud mpv-kvaliteetveinide klassi alandama, on esitatud lisas. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> In the case of a wine which has lost its status of quality wine psr by downgrading, the use of any indication reserved for quality wines psr on the labelling, packaging or official or commercial documents or in the records shall be prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti> Veinide puhul, mille mpv-kvaliteetveini staatus on klassi alandamise tulemusel &auml;ra v&otilde;etud, on keelatud kasutada etiketil, pakendil, ametlikes dokumentides, &auml;ridokumentides v&otilde;i registrites mpv-kvaliteetveini mis tahes m&auml;rget. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Competent bodies shall record the fact where the accompanying document covering a wine which is no longer entitled to the status of quality wine psr by downgrading is no longer appropriate. </inglise>
<eesti> P&auml;devad asutused registreerivad asjaolu, et dokument, mis on kaasas veiniga, millel ei ole klassi alandamise tulemusel enam mpv-kvaliteetveini staatust, ei ole enam asjakohane. </eesti>
<inglise> An entry indicating that the wine in question has lost its status of quality wine psr by downgrading shall be made in the registers of goods received and goods dispatched maintained by the holder of the wine. </inglise>
<eesti> Veini valdaja teeb kaupade liikumise registrisse kande selle kohta, et k&otilde;nealune vein on kaotanud klassi alandamise tulemusel mpv-kvaliteetveini staatuse. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> The Member States shall collect for each wine-growing year the information relating to the quantities of quality wines psr which have been downgraded on their geographical territory. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid koguvad teavet iga viinamarjakasvatusaasta l&otilde;ikes mpv-kvaliteetveinide koguste kohta, mille klassi on alandatud nende geograafilisel territooriumil. </eesti>
<inglise> They shall communicate this information to the Commission not later than 1 November each year. </inglise>
<eesti> Nad edastavad selle teabe komisjonile hiljemalt iga aasta 1. novembriks. </eesti>
<inglise> For this purpose they shall distinguish between the quantities of wine which have lost their status of quality wine psr: (a) at the production stage: </inglise>
<eesti> Selleks eristavad nad veinikoguseid, mis on kaotanud mpv-kvaliteetveini staatuse: a) tootmisetapil: </eesti>
<inglise> - on the initiative of the competent body, </inglise>
<eesti> - p&auml;deva asutuse algatusel, </eesti>
<inglise> - at the request of the producer; </inglise>
<eesti> - tootja taotlusel; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) at the marketing stage: </inglise>
<eesti> b) turustusetapil: </eesti>
<inglise> - on the initiative of the competent body, </inglise>
<eesti> - p&auml;deva asutuse algatusel, </eesti>
<inglise> - at the request of the trader. </inglise>
<eesti> - ettev&otilde;tja taotlusel. </eesti>
<inglise> They shall state the quantities in respect of which the status of table wine has been acknowledged. </inglise>
<eesti> Nad teatavad kogused, mille puhul on kinnitatud lauaveini staatus. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> Regulation (EEC) No 1697/70 is hereby repealed. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevaga tunnistatakse m&auml;&auml;rus (EM&Uuml;) nr 1697/70 kehtetuks. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on 1 January 1980. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub 1. jaanuaril 1980. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 20 December 1979. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 20. detsember 1979 </eesti>
<inglise> For the Commission Finn GUNDELACH Vice-President </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjoni nimel asepresident Finn GUNDELACH </eesti>
 